TeleSign Java SDK Documentation

The TeleSign Java SDK is a Java™ component that provides an interface to TeleSign Web Services.

See: Description

Packages 
Package Description
com.telesign.phoneid
Contains the PhoneId class, which abstracts calls to the TeleSign PhoneID Web Service.
com.telesign.phoneid.response
Contains a set of classes that represent TeleSign server response objects—one for each of the PhoneID web services.
com.telesign.util
Contains a class for normalizing a phone number, and a class that represents a TeleSign service request object.
com.telesign.verify
Contains the Verify class, which abstracts calls to the TeleSign Verify Web Service.
com.telesign.verify.response
Contains a class that represents the TeleSign server response object for the Phone Verify web service.

The TeleSign Java SDK is a Java™ component that provides an interface to TeleSign Web Services. It contains a Java class library that presents our web services in an intuitive, hierarchical object model, so you can create and manipulate them in the way you're accustomed. You can use this SDK to build TeleSign-based web applications in Java code, as MVC 3 web applications, using the Eclipse or NetBeans IDEs.
